        <briefdescription>
<para><verbatim>           [real, complex]
</verbatim> Set depending on whether the equalizer is running in real, complex mode. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Each of the eight channels consists of 2 sub-channels. In complex mode, the 2 sub-channels form a single filter channel acting on the data&apos;s real and imaginary parts. In real mode, the two sub-channels act as independent filter channels acting on the two real samples at the input. </para>        </detaileddescription>
